<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Italy were held to a hard-fought draw to kick-off their Nations League campaign as Inter Milan midfielder Stefano Sensi rescued a point.</p>

<p>The Italians dominated the game but struggled to find the net which led to Edin Dzeko opening the scoring for the visitors after 57 minutes. </p>

<p>Their lead lasted just ten minutes though when Sensi scored for the home side who could not go on to score a winner.</p>

<p>More to follow... </p>

<p>Edin Dzeko tucked the ball in against the run of play to give the visitors a shock advantage</p>

<p>The goal was Dzeko's 59th goal for his country in 108 caps since he first started back in 2007</p>

<p>Stefano Sensi celebrates with Nicolo Barella after scoring an equaliser for Italy against Bosnia</p>

<p>Federico Chiesa fires a shot agonizingly wide as Italy looked to get themselves back on terms</p>

<p>Roberto Mancini was frustrated as hit Italy squad struggled to put away their many chances</p>
